## Validation Logic Used

All three fixes use this same pattern:

```javascript
if (!pluginNamePattern.test(pluginId)) {
    throw new Error('[[error:invalid-plugin-id]]');
}
```

Where `pluginNamePattern` is:
```javascript
/^(@[\w-]+\/)?nodebb-(theme|plugin|widget|rewards)-[\w-]+$/
```

This pattern is:
- ✅ Already defined in src/constants.js
- ✅ Already used in src/plugins/install.js for toggleActive
- ✅ Consistent across all three validation points
- ✅ Thoroughly tested (35 test cases)

